    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Besan Cheela is a savory Indian pancake made with gram flour, onions, and fresh herbs. It's quick to prepare and a healthy option for breakfast or snacks.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>15 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup besan (gram flour)</li>
        <li>1 onion (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>1 green chili (chopped)</li>
        <li>Chopped coriander leaves</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Water as required</li>
        <li>Oil for cooking</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, mix besan, onion, chili, coriander, turmeric, and salt.</li>
        <li>Add water gradually to form a smooth, pourable batter.</li>
        <li>Heat a non-stick pan and lightly grease with oil.</li>
        <li>Pour a ladle of batter and spread it into a circle.</li>
        <li>Cook on both sides until golden brown using a little oil.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with green chutney or ketchup.</li>
    </ol>
